Betty Friedan's legacy as a feminist pioneer and author of "The Feminine Mystique" continues to inspire progress for women's rights.
Her groundbreaking work challenged societal norms and paved the way for modern feminism.
Friedan's dedication to gender equality and advocacy for the Equal Rights Amendment left a lasting impact on American society.
Despite criticism and controversy, her contributions to the women's movement are undeniable.
Friedan's personal struggles and achievements resonate with women of all generations, highlighting the ongoing fight for gender equality and empowerment.
Her work remains a cornerstone of feminist literature and a testament to the enduring importance of women's rights.
